<dec f='include/boost/program_options/options_description.hpp' l='114' type='std::string boost::program_options::option_description::canonical_display_name(int canonical_option_style = 0) const'/>
<doc f='include/boost/program_options/options_description.hpp' l='107'>/** Returns the canonical name for the option description to enable the user to
            recognised a matching option.
            1) For short options (&apos;-&apos;, &apos;/&apos;), returns the short name prefixed.
            2) For long options (&apos;--&apos; / &apos;-&apos;) returns the first long name prefixed
            3) All other cases, returns the first long name (if present) or the short
               name, unprefixed.
        */</doc>
